News24 Correspondent (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Vereeniging - A driver has been killed and a passenger left seriously injured after they crashed into a tree while travelling in a bakkie in Vereeniging on New Year&rsquo;s Day, said paramedics.&ldquo;It is understood that the driver lost control of the vehicle, causing it to smash into the tree and eject the one passenger,&rdquo; said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring. When paramedics arrived at the scene on Sunday morning, the vehicle was found up against a large tree. One of the men was found trapped in the driver&rsquo;s seat and was declared dead on the scene.His body was retrieved using the jaws-of-life.The other man was found lying outside the bakkie. He had sustained numerous injuries and was in a serious condition. He was stabilised on the scene before being taken to hospital.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.